name: Republic of Korea Air Force Airbus A330 MRTT Departure from Calgary Airport
description:
A rare visitor! This aircraft stopped in Calgary as a fuel stop on delivery from Spain to South Korea, a bit of a surprise as these aircraft were apparently supposed to fly through Vancouver. Not complaining!

This is the second Airbus A330 MRTT (Multi-Role Tanker/Transport) for the Republic of Korea Air Force, departing for Gimhae Air Base in South Korea this morning! Enjoy this brand new military A330 departing Calgary, a bit different from our usual ones from the Royal Air Force.
